thinking: The user consults a notebook which outlines a pipetting plan. The notebook shows a grid for a 96-well plate with columns '1', '2', '3' and row 'A'. The instructions are to add 30uL of 'Reagent A' to well A1, 30uL of 'Reagent B' to well A2, and 30uL of 'Reagent C' to well A3. The user sets a single-channel pipette to 30 uL (display shows '030'). Following the plan, they use a fresh tip to aspirate liquid from the first microcentrifuge tube (inferred to be Reagent A) and dispense it into well A1. They discard the tip. They then use another fresh tip to aspirate from the second tube (inferred to be Reagent B) and dispense it into well A2. Finally, they use a third fresh tip to aspirate from the third tube (inferred to be Reagent C) and dispense it into well A3, completing the planned transfers.
